s hassenfeld was the first female president of the american jewish joint distribution committee jdc from  to  in this position she helped to found the international development program idp a nonsectarian emergency aid organization in response to the december  armenian earthquake the charter flights bringing severely injured earthquake victims to israel marked the first time that the jdc offered crisis help to nonjews also in  she oversaw the jdc’s return to the soviet union the first time the organization had been in the soviet union since the dissolution of the agrojoint in  hassenfeld through the jdc was involved with the rescue of serbs croats muslims and jews from sarajevo during the breakup of yugoslavia in the early s and aided jewish outreach in central and eastern europe including the resettling in various countries of jews leaving after the breakup of the soviet union she also oversaw jdc operations in the middle east and africa most dramatically the  operation solomon airlift rescue of over  ethiopian jews bringing them to settle in israel awards and accoladesedit sylvia hassenfeld received numerous awards and honors in recognition of more than fifty years of national and international philanthropic and humanitarian leadership the hassenfeld family was very closely connected with brandeis university from its earliest days including her fatherinlaw husband and her children she received an honorary doctorate in humane letters from brandeis university in  in “recognition of her leadership activism and philanthropy” she was made an honorary citizen of jerusalem a presidential appointee to the united states holocaust memorial council was awarded the  emma lazarus statue of liberty award by the american jewish historical society and was honored by the national conference of christians and jews sylvia k hassenfeld died on saturday august   at her home in manhattan she was  referencesedit  sylvia hassenfeld trustee former board vice chair dies  brandeisnow brandei